translated: Kjellberg, Carl Ossian, merchant, Gothenburg, born on September 30th, 1875 in Gothenburg to consul, merchant Carl-August K. and Eliza Gibson. Married on the 13th of a month with Lilly Swedenborg. Children: Carl, born in 1915, attaché at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in Stockholm; Stig, born in 1918, economist in Stockholm; Birgitta, born in 1922. Completed a masters' examination in 1893. Worked as a clerk at Goteborgs Enskilda Bank from 1893 to 1895, employed at bank and trade offices in Hamburg, London, and Paris from 1896 to 1897, became a co-owner of T. A. Kjellberg & Sons in 1896, chairman of J. A. Kjellberg & Sons Ltd. since 1925. Member of the board for Kjellbergska Girls' School from 1902 to 1943, vice-chairman from 1929 to 1943, member of the board for Kjellbergska Commercial Girls' School since 1943, Gothenburg Savings Bank from 1909 to 1946, Ocean Insurance Co. Ltd. since 1910, Gothenburg Gas and Electricity Works from 1912 to 1925, Gothenburg City Hospital since 1915, trade council member in Gothenburg from 1924 to 1935, Gothenburg Commercial Institute from 1925 to 1942, vice-chairman there from 1939 to 1942, member of the board for Gothenburg Horticultural Society, former member of the board for Billerud AB, Björneborgs Railway AB, and others, honorary member of The Bachelors Club. Japanese consul from 1913 to 1933. Recipient of the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO), Royal Order of Vasa (RVO), Commander of the Order of the Lion of Judah (JHS04kl.), and Commander of the Order of the Polar Star (US05kl.).
